          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Riding through microclimates demands layers that can breathe on the move, especially in spring and summer when conditions can shift mid-ride. At Ornot, we think in three parts: a next-to-skin layer to manage moisture, a breathable midlayer for light insulation, and a lightweight outer layer for wind or fog. The goal is simple: start slightly cool, adjust with effort, and stay comfortable as the ride warms up.</p>",
